entries.femaleVariant: I know as much as you do. All she said was to come here. She'll either find us or she left us something…
We have new variables to consider. Peralez's campaign, the investigation...
Weldon Holt. How's your campaign against Peralez goin'?
How's the campaign going?
I don't know you, but enjoy your evening.
Here as well, Hands?
Mr. Hands? Here?
What’s so surprising about me being here, getting invited? Hansen's always been a civil, reasonable man.
Gillean Jordan and Arif Iqbal? In the flesh and together, no less. Just wanted to say hi.
Hey.
It was carried out just as we agreed.
Yeah, all the hottest markets.
Mr. Kavorkin…
Mr. Kavorkin?
All of this is up for grabs.
Hey, haven’t I seen you on the feeds? Warning people about the Relic?
Seen you on TV.
No, no, I know that it was specially done for us. Payment is not what's at issue – I just need the paperwork to go with it.
Is there no alternative?
Here's the deal – either we get some proof of purchase, or there's another path – non-violent, I should add.
Meaning what, exactly?
Meaning you sue us, take us to court. Put on a show for the people.
I'm prepared to testify that this, erm... "undertaking" was commissioned by City Hall.
We will discuss this at a later time.
Of course. I'm always open to compromise…
Oh, it's hardly a contest. I'd say our victory is assured. But still – don't forget to vote!
Gillean, dear... There’s nothing smart about shooting your boss down over your own turf! Not to mention proving incapable of then finishing the job…
Keep your fucking voice down!
You were just singing Hansen’s praises for his civility. Are we now back to “scary maniac”?
Ah, say what you want, Arif. Just don’t come crying if you get kicked out of the party of the year.
Pfft. You’re the one accusing him of attempting to murder President  Rosalind Myers. In front of millions of viewers, no less.
That's the job, as we all know – fucking reading words off a prompter for the gonk masses. Whereas here, my friend, here words actually matter.
Umm... Hey.
No, you imbecile. I’m the chief of the NC-fucking-PD, not some busboy! My cut's thirty percent. I won't get the financing otherwise.
I want three more shipments before the end of the month.
Three’s a lot.
This is not up for debate. Either you set up three for takedown, or tomorrow morning, we start kicking down your doors.
Analysis, information integration, candlestick patterns detection, indicator search...
Sure, it's free. Veeery funny. Who do you think I am?
Well, no, it's just supposed to look free. That's the whole angle!
We'll talk more tomorrow, Mom. Yeah, love you too. Bye.
Uuh, do I know you?
Sorry, I have an important holo to make...
All of it?
Except for Heywood.
What about Santo Domingo?
Nobody cares about Santo Domingo.
My people tell me that all land transit to and from Night City passes through here.
Who cares about land transit? We own the port, the docks, the airport...
The airport's also ours. Let the nomads battle over the highway with 6th Street.
I could make two million a day on Metroplex runs alone. You and my friends over there – all we would need to do is team up.
Hmm... we'll have to think about it.
God's light shine upon you.
Yes? What is it?
Umm... where were we?
Ah, fuck. What now?
Err... yes? What is it?
I'm so sorry. What was I saying…?
Oh... you again?
So I took her to a clinic and I told them to do a full face plate conversion. Whatever she wants – just do it.
I. Don't. Care! If she wants a gator's face – fine! Throw in a nice set of sharp, white teeth while you're at it, huh?
Know what they said? "Exotics went out of style three decades ago. Thee days everybody wants..." Well, you know what.
Welcome!
A pleasant evening to you.
Would you care for some champagne?
[Take] Yes, please.
Don't mind if I do.
And you – what's your play?
I'll grab a drink and look around. Open line on comms.
Don't press anyone too hard. We need to keep up appearances. Look like you're having fun.
[Sit down] Wine.
[Sit down] Something strong.
Centzon Tequila.
Can I get a double shot of Centzon Tequila?
Hit me with somethin' strong.
Glass of grape tears, please.
[Drink]
Ah, that's the stuff…
Alsatian Pinot Noir, straight from the warm bosom of Europe.
Impressive as headpieces go. Same kind Lizzy Wizzy was wearing.
Japanese whiskey, perhaps? I have an excellent single malt.
It's not about your upbringing! Look, I'm a self-made man. Borrowed a hundred grand from my parents and invested it. In myself.
Didn't go spending it all on syncoke and expensive ass, but on implants and training. Gave it all back the second I could.
Exactly. It's about self-discipline and ambition. If you're poor, you really have no one to blame but yourself.
Hey, you look a little lost…
Familiar face – from the media feeds.
Thanks for your concern.
Ruth Dzeng?
Appreciate the concern, but I'm good.
The one and only. You wouldn't feel like… keeping me company for the rest of the evening, would you?
Night's still young. Later, maybe.
Whatever you say. Enjoy your evening.
OK, just one more…
I'm afraid you're short of luck on that one. But I can offer you a glass of wine, or fine liqueur.
I assure you, our selection of spirits surpasses even that of Night City's best establishments.
Would you care for some champagne?
Gin-'n'-tonic, please. Say... I'm lookin' for a friend, she was supposed to meet me here.
Yes?
You look exactly like my friend Goro Takemura.
Did he also just get out of rehab?
You look like a friend of mine.
Got it as a gift, from Lizzy.
Yeah, actually the same exact one. She gave it to me.
Bask in its glory, mere mortal.
Preem, isn't it?
Would you care for a drink?
Come back if you need anything!
Here you are.
[Leave]
What a headdress! Are you one of the dancers?
[Lean]
Can't see shit…
[Stop leaning]
He's in rehab now, actually.
He lost his employer.
Truth be told, he's goin' through a kind of rehab himself. His family turned their backs on him, he lost his home, his implants…
Lost his employer, recently. They were close. He's adjusting to his new life. Not easy for a guy like him.
entries.maleVariant: Lost his employer recently. They were close. He's adjusting to his new life. Not easy for a guy like him.

entries.femaleVariant: Tragic... But such are the consequences of addiction. I have been through it all.
He's dead.
Tell him not to lose hope. If one is industrious, there is no shortage of work in Night City.
Maybe your friend would like to try his hand at show business? I could use a double for rainy days…
Hmm... Might actually take you up on that. I'll let him know.
Watch out! I will hold you to your word!
Sadly, he is no longer with us.
entries.maleVariant: Sadly, he's... no longer with us.

entries.femaleVariant: I am sorry to hear that. Please accept my condolences.
Thanks.
If I can help in any way, you need only let me know…
You're the one with the plan.
Thought you were the master planner here…
Well, aren't you special.
Indeed. It's better if we're not seen together.
What now?
Evidently I am.
Right, OK…
Just saw Hands. Felt to me like he's here on a mission of his own.
He likely is. Or just tendin' the business, gatherin' intel…
NCPD chief's cuttin' a deal with the 6th Street boss. Not even tryin' to hide it.
Party's a microcosm of Night City. NCPD's a gang like any other, except it's listed on the stock exchange.
Scale of biz bein' conducted here… Just overheard an arms deal, enough gear to outfit a private army.
I'm not surprised. Look around, run your eyes over the faces, regalia – you've got foreign ambassadors, banana republic dictators, revolutionaries-in-waiting, corporate heads…
We need equipment that can withstand and remain reliable in extremely low temperatures.
Our Argentinian friends made me aware of that. We've reached an initial agreement for thirty air defense systems, five hundred armored vehicles and one hundred combat AVs.
In addition to that, personnel equipment for five thousand operators as well as two nuclear submarines. Twenty-seventy-eight is our current ETA.
Hm… OK. Does your "friend" have a name?
Song So Mi. Korean lady, around thirty.
Hmm… Might've seen her around, on this floor, I think.
Let's party...?
I'll look for Songbird.
Think I’m startin' to feel the vibe…
Just remember what we're here for.
Gonna stroll and mingle. Might spot her in the crowd.
Good idea.
A little late. What about testing?
It's the testing that determines the date. You can have everything by January, but with lower-quality testing.
I understand. We'll iron out the details, I'm sure.
It's precisely those kinds of needs Hansen and company are here to fulfill.
This isn't about who has the right credentials. You just have to speak Hansen's language.
You think Hansen'll agree to revitalize ten percent of the Zone because of a few trumped-up military slogans?
That's not what I mean. He needs to be shown his projected profits and losses in plain writing, without any sugarcoating.
So you think I'm sugarcoating?
You signed a contract with Night City – well done. Just leave Hansen to me, because no offense – I know you'll find a way to cock it up.
Ah, the dream of restoring Pacifica to its intended glory lives on. Overheard some investors…
[Inform Reed] Even that televangelist is here.
Even the pastor warnin' peeps about the Relic on the feeds made an appearance.
Lots of faces familiar off the media feeds…
Maybe he's here to save Hansen. Or collect donations for his church – end of the day, blood money's still money.
Ready to watch their cash disappear into Hansen's pockets? Brave of them.
They wouldn't miss this for the world. It's an adrenaline kick, they get off on it. And Hansen gets off on havin' them eat out of his hand.
[Drink]
[Drink]
[Stand]
[Drink]
[Drink]
[Drink]
[Drink]
[Drink]
[Drink]
[Drink]
[Drink]
I’ll be at the bar if you need me.
Gotta hand it to Hansen, V... Party's  hoppin', has a sense of grandeur. Didn't have shit like this in my day…
Now hop on over there and help me out – managed to forget what real champagne tastes like…
[Inform Reed] Ran into Hands.
[Inform Reed] NCPD’s makin' a deal with 6th Street.
[Inform Reed] Seein' loads of celebrities..
[Inform Reed] Sheer scale of business done here… Sheesh.
[Inform Reed] Saw some investors lookin' a little like fish outta water…
Aim to get fucked up on Hansen’s dime, then puke all over his carpets? Respect.
So, Alaska... and now what? You putting all that kit back on the market? Or you got a buyer lined up already?
Wouldn't mind offloading the IFVs to some statelet. Time for an upgrade, know what I mean? And the rest… I got use for it. Eyein' this piece of turf, ripe for the plucking.
Hmm... in our back yard somewhere?

Fuckin' hyenas, each and every one. Tellin' ya, won’t be long now we'll be hearin' about "dangerous terrorists" in Myanmar threatening our way of life. Then about the "urgent need to install a democratic government" there…
You watch, Hansen'll jerk us around for hours, or try to. Thinks the booze and ambiance softens us up, makes us pliable for when we sit down to negotiate.
I don't think I care either way. We have one job – to get two thousand bums and vagrants out of Vista del Rey. How we get it done? The bosses don't care.
Just in case you're still wonderin' why I hate corporats and politiwhores... you're a hired gun and petty thief, but I'd say your presence at this party is still raisin' the moral bar.
To my right. Booth far back, behind the stairs. the guy in fatigues, looks like he came here straight from a firing range.
Owner of the Black Sapphire, Mr. D-town himself. Kurt Hansen. Clearly havin' a great night in the company of the NCPD commissioner.
PA broadcasts? He’s fiercely anti-law enforcement. It's an act. Behind closed doors, he's rubbin' elbows and pattin' backs with NCPD’s top brass.
So, Kurt Hansen, duke of Dogtown, in the flesh. More mutt than alpha hound, looks like.
V, this guy looks exactly like your ronin. Un-fuckin'-canny... Sure that ain’t Takemura?

In my day, no competition – Soviet mob was the worst scum. Human trafficking, murder for hire, torture-based debt collection... Shit sounds bad as is, but they actually managed to turn the horror up a notch.
Enjoy.
<kiroshi l="mex" o="Salud, amiga." t="Cheers, friend." b="" a=""/>
entries.maleVariant: <kiroshi l="mex" o="Salud, amigo." t="Cheers, friend." b="" a=""/>

entries.femaleVariant: Your drink's up.
Here you are.
Seems your special agent has special needs. Tryin' to drown his sins and sorrows.
Agh, Wendy O. Williams...  toughest-ass rockergirl ever. Took her own life when I was nine. Were she here, she’d fuckin' burn the stage down, blow everyone and everything up to high heaven.
This table is full. Please join another. Thank you.
We should be asking who's not here. NCPD comissioner, politicians, diplomats, celebrities, corp execs, gang bosses…
You claim Kurt was pleased. So I'm puzzled why he witheld his support, if only in your negotiations with the bald twerp from the consulate.
I saw you… simping for that mangy slut from N54.
Well... here goes nothin’!
No more gambling, this I swear. Starting tomorrow…
Come on, come on! One more win! Just one more!
Breathe, relax. The system is foolproof...
The same? Again? Unbelievable…
The table is being prepared. Betting will resume in minutes.
Stage is off limits. Step away, please.
Sorry, I can't let you go any further.
Stage entrance – artists only.
Move away from the stage. Now, please.
Election was tough. Too bad you lost.
Mister Holt! Election come and gone... you wound up on the short end. How ya holdin' up?
Well... I don't treat it as a loss, you see. To me, it's a... minor setback.
The beautiful and exotic Myanmar. Politically, country's a mess, but the gemstone deposits... Rubies, jade, sapphires... Drool just thinkin' about it.
We'll burn some villages, nab some warlords, put their heads out on spikes... you know, just generally take charge.
I’ll drink to that.
Hiring Hansen and hounds'll be cheapest. No corporate overhead, his prices're lowest, just... structurally.
What do you think he’ll do with them?
I don't care, do you? Please…
Avoid him, especially any confrontation. Besides that, stay visible. Songbird said she’d find us here, let's give her a chance.
I just fucking lost it. I’m talking myself hoarse for serious sums, and some ripperquack is gonna explain fashion trends to my daughter?!
In the end, they shut their traps and gave me a discount. But... I had to disown her. I mean, if she wants to inherit my money, she'll have to look like human royalty. Any other mods? On her now.
I think he wished to appear neutral. For public consumption, of course.
We didn’t put two ministers behind bars to have him "appear neutral" now. That ship has sailed. Mumbai branch is losing patience fast. Remind him tomorrow.
Naturally, of course.
Honey, I was just being nice.
They don't pay you to be nice. You're supposed to be tending to business. You know I could tell Carlos I talked to the cartel alone again ‘cause my husband caught a whiff of available pussy.
Tell you what – I'll talk to Carlos. Just so happens the “mangy slut from N54” disclosed some shit he'll be very interested in hearing. Honey.
An' I need to know this because…?
I'd give all the parties I ever went to, including this one, to see her live and in concert just once. That’s why. Now let’s delta the fuck outta here while you still got the chance.
Was she alone?
Was she…? No, no. She was with Colonel Hansen, I think. But he’s in sight, with other people now, and she ain't one of 'em.
Yeah, I can see that. Have one on me later, yeah?
Thanks! As you wish, sir.
Say again? Maintenance area? Where exactly? Wounded or do we have bodies?
<kiroshi l="mex" o="Vaya... Es mucho más hermosa en persona..." t=" Wow... she’s even more beautiful in real life…" b="" a=""/>
Incredible! Just… dazzling!
Bravo! Braaa-vo!
That's a preem getup!
Hell yeah, Lizzy!
Fuck... Yes, sir, I will... Affirmative. Four and Seven will shift posts immediately. Out.

Well, Hansen’s clearly made it. It's literally as if he's defecating truffles and caviar, while they've all lined up to hold their plates up to his arse. I mean, they want to gobble up what he's serving.
Thanks.
'Preciate it. Thanks.
Thanks a lot.
